description: You are in a whirlwind, where objects fly past you and into you!
The great storm pulls at you, tearing at your clothing and equipment
mercilessly.  As the wind subsides for a moment, you are able to
examine your surroundings.  The storm continues in all directions
except below you, where The Sanctuary of the Cathedral lies, and to
the east, where a precipitous balcony rests.  As you are about to take
action to escape, the storm tugs at you again...!

20252.name: Altar of Destruction
description: You stand at the Altar of Talos, the Stormlord.  Behind the altar,
tapestries line the walls.  One depicting Talos, a bearded man with
one eye, shows a hurricane crashing down upon a large city.  As you
watch, the hurricane seems to begin moving and destroying the city
which begins burning, turning into ruins.  There is a dark chalice on
the table before you, filled to the brim in blood and gore.  An eerie
presence is also here, undetectable, tugging at your very lifeforce.
Exits lead South, East, West, and Up into the roiling maelstrom above
you.

20269.name: Before The Altar
description: Before you stands the unholy Altar of Talos.  Black candles stand
on the altar and a table before it, each one pouring down an ebon
ichor remarkably similar to human blood.  Skulls of various humanoids
line the base of the altar, their eyesockets glowing hollowly.  A
procession of priests form a line before the altar, seeming to draw
you inextricably into their ranks.  If you don't join them, they will
most certainly destroy you.  If you do join them, you must drink from
a chalice on the table ahead.  You can only guess what fluids it may
contain.  Exits lie east, south, west, and up into the maelstrom
swirling above you.

20250.name: Cathedral Guardian~
description:
A huge knight stands as the guardian to the door of the Cathedral of
Destruction.  His black plate mail is covered with an assortment of spikes. 
The symbol of Talos, the Storm Lord, emblazon its breastplate.  Electricity
coarses through its body, occasionaly flickering between his plate armor.

20289.name: Rahvin {&T{7he {&E{7lkhunter{x~
description:
A large, yellow toothed, wary-eyed creature stands before you. 
Drawn to full height, he appears only around 5 feet tall.  His long
topknot hangs over his shoulder and lies beside the long pike he
carries.  When wielded in his capable hands, the pike is not a weapon
to be trifled over.  An agile male, Rahvin seems able to manipulate
the pike as if it were a part of himself.  Beware!  For DESTRUCTION
shall come to all!
